{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d53b02f7-9c68-484b-bb5e-60d7ec27f12f","content":"This is a TUnit project using Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP). TUnit uses `--treenode-filter` with a hierarchical path format (`/Assembly/Namespace/Class/Test`).\n\nThe command to run only `SmsNotificationTests`:\n\n```\ndotnet test -- --treenode-filter \"/*/*/SmsNotificationTests/*\"\n```\n\n- `--` separates `dotnet test` args from MTP args\n- `/*/*/` wildcards match any assembly and namespace\n- `SmsNotificationTests` matches the class\n- `/*` matches all test methods in that class\n\nThis will run `SendSms_HealthCheck` and `SendSms_ValidPhone_Succeeds`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"813bc3a5-b194-476b-990a-0da9b217a73e","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"This is a TUnit project. TUnit uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) natively. For TUnit with MTP, the filter syntax is different from VSTest. TUnit uses `--treenode-filter` for filtering tests.\n\nTo filter by class name in TUnit, the command would use `--treenode-filter` with the appropriate syntax. The treenode filter for a class in TUnit looks like:\n\n```\ndotnet test --treenode-filter \"/*/*/SmsNotificationTests\"\n```\n\nOr more specifically, TUnit's treenode filter uses a path-like syntax: `/assembly/namespace/class/test`\n\n\nThe correct syntax for filtering by class name is `/*/*/SmsNotificationTests` or `/*/*/SmsNotificationTests/*` depending on whether you want to match the class itself or all tests within it. Both `dotnet test` and `dotnet run` work with this filter format. I'm verifying the treenode filter structure for TUnit—the path format is `/AssemblyName/Namespace/ClassName/TestName`, so using wildcards for assembly and namespace while specifying the class name and matching all tests within it should work correctly. Let me double-check this approach before finalizing the answer.","outputTokens":897,"requestId":"D006:33D9D0:153A905:189F522:69EC1707"},"id":"f122d134-9e94-4421-a47e-15d9915a8aa3","timestamp":"2026-04-25T01:21:28.568Z","parentId":"f8444309-48d7-4ce8-a1ad-fdec67167213"}
